{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Taking writing education part as an example, college students in Guo and Li's research reflected that chatbots could enhance their learning motivation [14], but Woo et. al.",
    "'s research shows that middle students cooperating with ChatGPT will not inspire them but could lead to higher cognitive load [15].",
    "Considering the differences between college students and middle school students, researchers can explore more on the application methods that are more suitable for each of these groups separately, as well as focus on groups of other age ranges.Lastly, the choices of LLMs in the studies on writing education are ChatGPT series, which cannot represent the overall performances of LLMs.",
    "Except for two studies that used Platform for Open Exploration (Poe) to access other LLMs or customize chatbots [14,15], all other studies focused on writing use ChatGPT directly [11][12][13].",
    "Even though ChatGPT is the most powerful LLM for now, the customizing chatbots function on Poe platforms also has the special advantage of allowing chatbots to meet students' specific requirements, improving learners' writing skills and motivations [14]."
  ],
